hopobject.body: What do you want to do when you've finished? a5 pharmacy OD, a green sea turtle swims in a husbandry tank Thursday, July 25, 2013, at The Shark Reef Aquarium at Mandalay Resort and Casino in Las Vegas. Thursday, the turtle was shipped some 2,400-miles, via FedEx, from the Florida Keys-based Turtle Hospital where it had been cared for for almost five years. The reptile can’t be released because of a irreparable collapsed lung and is to live out its life in the Vegas aquarium’s 1.3-million-gallon exhibition tank. (Darrin Bush/Las Vegas News Bureau)
